9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 257, L.D. 403, “An Act to Protect
10 Holders of Distressed Mortgages from Fraud”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 1.
12 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 5 and inserting the following:
13 'Sec. 5. Effective date. This Act takes effect January 1, 2026.'
14 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
15 number to read consecutively.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This amendment strikes the provisions in the bill that prohibit a mortgagee from
1188 enforcing a mortgage, including the initiation of a foreclosure action, if the notice of the
1199 right to cure default is more than 90 days old. The amendment also establishes an effective
2200 date of January 1, 2026.
